<%= content_for :title do %>
  HEY World alternative — blog by email from any inbox — Pagecord
<% end %>

<%= content_for :og_image do %>
  <%= dynamic_og_image_for_landing_page(title: "A Better HEY World Alternative") %>
<% end %>

<%= content_for :meta_description do %>
  A HEY World alternative that works with Gmail, Fastmail, iCloud, Proton — any inbox. Plus pages, themes, custom domains, RSS, and export.
<% end %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <h1 class="source-serif font-semibold text-center text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">
    HEY World is great if you live in HEY. Pagecord works from any inbox.
  </h1>

  <div class="md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4">
    <p class="mt-8 md:mt-12">
      HEY World gets one thing very right: publishing from email feels natural. If HEY is already your home, that simplicity is lovely.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pagecord keeps the email-to-blog magic but removes the inbox lock-in. Use Gmail, Fastmail, iCloud, Proton Mail, Outlook, or whatever you already have, then add pages, themes, custom domains, RSS, newsletters, analytics, and export.
    </p>
    <p>
      Classic is free forever. Premium is $<%= localised_price %>/year.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-8 mb-4 md:text-xl">
    <%= link_to new_signup_path do %>
      <div class="mt-2 inline-flex font-medium p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm btn-primary text-xl">Start free</div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "comparison_intro", sections: [
  {
    title: "Who this is for",
    paragraphs: [
      "People who love the idea of posting by email but do not want to move their whole email life to one provider.",
      "Small personal sites, field notes, status updates, project logs, family blogs, and any blog where the fastest editor is your inbox."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "Why people switch",
    paragraphs: [
      "HEY World is tied to HEY. That's clean if you're already there, but a non-starter if your email lives somewhere else.",
      "It's also intentionally narrow. Pagecord keeps the simplicity but gives your site more room to grow beyond a stream of emailed posts."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "What is different",
    paragraphs: [
      "Every Pagecord blog gets a private posting address. Send an email, publish a post. Use the web editor when you want more control.",
      "Any inbox in, a real website out — with RSS, custom domains, subscribers, pages, themes, and export."
    ]
  }
] %>

